trans-unit.source: Exposes <xref href="System.Windows.UIElement3D"></xref> types to [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)].

By default, any class that inherits from <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> uses UIElement3DAutomationPeer to communicate with [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)].
If you create a class that inherits from <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D>, you may want to provide an automation peer to support the functionality of your class.

Override the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetClassNameCore%2A> method to return a string that represents the type of the element associated with the UIElement3DAutomationPeer.

For example, if you create a class called `My3DElement` and an automation peer called `My3DElementAutomationPeer`, override the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetClassNameCore%2A> method to return the string "My3DElement".

If your class matches one of the known control types, override the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetAutomationControlTypeCore%2A> method to return that <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType>.

Note that although the existing <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType> values are generally associated with 2D controls, the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType> indicates a control's functionality, not its appearance.

So if your <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> invokes an action when the user clicks it, you probably want <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.GetHelpTextCore%2A> to return <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ControlType.Button?displayProperty=fullName>.
The behavior of your custom <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> determines what other methods you should override.
Each method topic in the UIElement3DAutomationPeer describes how the method is used and when it is appropriate to override it.
UIElement3DAutomationPeer is introduced in the .NET Framework version 3.5.
For more information, see [Versions and Dependencies](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).

This <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer> remains in memory until the associated <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> is destroyed.

The same instance of the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer> is returned from subsequent calls to this method and to calls to <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer.FromElement%2A>.
The type of the peer is determined by the <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D.OnCreateAutomationPeer%2A> virtual callback.
If <xref:System.Windows.UIElement3D> does not implement the callback, no <xref:System.Windows.Automation.Peers.UIElement3DAutomationPeer> is created and this method returns `null`.
